#  Student Grade System (Bash Script)

A terminal-based grading system written in Bash, designed for simplicity, clarity, and impact. This project allows users to input student marks, calculate averages, assign grades, and manage recordsâ€”all from the command line. Built for educational use and CLI-based project presentations.

---

## ðŸš€ Features

- Add student details and calculate total, average, and grade
- Display student summary in spreadsheet-style table
- Save all entries to a CSV file (`grades.csv`)
- View all student records in a formatted table
- Search for a student by name
- Password-protected admin access for viewing and searching
- Clean, bilingual-ready structure for future localization

---

##  Requirements

- Bash shell (Linux, macOS, or online Bash compiler)
- No external dependencies (no `bc`, no GUI tools)

